<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Barbell-Bent-Over-Rows">Barbell Bent Over Rows</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/barbell-bent-over-row" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Barbell bent over rows</a> focus on the lats, rhomboids, traps, rear delts, and biceps. It is an excellent pull up alternative for back development. This explains why it’s a favorite back exercise among bodybuilders! They often include it in their <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/compound-bicep-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">compound bicep exercises</a>.</p>



<p>It involves pulling the barbell horizontally towards your torso. This position can reduce the strain on the shoulders, which may not be possible during pull ups. Also, exercises like barbell rows that involve pulling and pinching the shoulder blades together effectively <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5684019/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">improve rounded shoulders.</a></p>



<p>This can be beneficial for athletes and individuals working a desk job alike.</p>



